\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {SWA-MPPI pipeline overview.} \textbf  {Left panel:} Persona construction. For each target country, WVS Wave~7 statistics are used to parameterise three age-cohort personas (young, middle-aged, older) capturing within-country variation in gender egalitarianism, religious importance, personal autonomy, and meritocratic orientation, plus a country-invariant utilitarian persona. \textbf  {Middle panel:} Batched forward pass. The scenario $\mathbf  {x}$, prefixed by each of the $N=4$ persona system prompts and the baseline empty prompt, is evaluated in a single batched call to the frozen LLM $f_\theta $. Two passes with swapped group orderings are performed for positional debiasing. Raw \texttt  {LEFT}/\texttt  {RIGHT} logit pairs $\mathbf  {z}_i$ are extracted from the last-position output tensor for each agent. \textbf  {Right panel:} MPPI optimisation loop. If inter-agent variance $\nu = \operatorname  {Var}(\delta _1,\ldots  ,\delta _N)$ exceeds the calibrated threshold $\tau ^{(c)}$, $K=128$ scalar perturbations $\epsilon _k$ are sampled and scored by the Prospect-Theory-weighted collective utility $U_{\text  {total}}(\epsilon _k)$. Importance-weighted summation yields the optimal correction $\delta ^*$; the final decision probability is $p_{\text  {spare}} = \sigma ((\bar  \delta + \delta ^*)/T_{\text  {dec}})$. }}{8}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:overview}{{1}{8}{\textbf {SWA-MPPI pipeline overview.} \textbf {Left panel:} Persona construction. For each target country, WVS Wave~7 statistics are used to parameterise three age-cohort personas (young, middle-aged, older) capturing within-country variation in gender egalitarianism, religious importance, personal autonomy, and meritocratic orientation, plus a country-invariant utilitarian persona. \textbf {Middle panel:} Batched forward pass. The scenario $\mathbf {x}$, prefixed by each of the $N=4$ persona system prompts and the baseline empty prompt, is evaluated in a single batched call to the frozen LLM $f_\theta $. Two passes with swapped group orderings are performed for positional debiasing. Raw \texttt {LEFT}/\texttt {RIGHT} logit pairs $\mathbf {z}_i$ are extracted from the last-position output tensor for each agent. \textbf {Right panel:} MPPI optimisation loop. If inter-agent variance $\nu = \operatorname {Var}(\delta _1,\ldots ,\delta _N)$ exceeds the calibrated threshold $\tau ^{(c)}$, $K=128$ scalar perturbations $\epsilon _k$ are sampled and scored by the Prospect-Theory-weighted collective utility $U_{\text {total}}(\epsilon _k)$. Importance-weighted summation yields the optimal correction $\delta ^*$; the final decision probability is $p_{\text {spare}} = \sigma ((\bar \delta + \delta ^*)/T_{\text {dec}})$}{figure.caption.13}{}}
